<plot>A short in the Memories From Melody Lane series. This dramatization of 'Stephen Foster (III)' (qv)'s life shows how the songwriter came to write four of his most popular tunes: "My Old Kentucky Home", "Old Folks at Home", "Beautiful Dreamer", and " De Camptown Races". After each song is performed, the audience is invited to sing along with the Melody Makers as the lyrics are displayed on title cards.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?333601</url></doc>
